setup:
git config --global user.name "Your Name"
git config --global user.email "you@example.com"
starting:
git init                  # Start a new repo
git clone URL             # Clone an existing repo
everyday workflow:
git status                # Show changes
git add file              # Stage file
git add .                 # Stage all
git commit -m "Message"   # Commit staged changes
git log --oneline         # Show commit history
branching:
git branch                # List branches
git branch name           # Create branch
git checkout name         # Switch branch
git switch -c name        # Create + switch
git merge name            # Merge branch into current
remote:
git remote -v             # Show remotes
git push origin branch    # Push branch
git pull origin branch    # Pull updates
git fetch                 # Get remote info without merge
undo/fix:
git restore file          # Discard changes
git reset --hard HEAD     # Reset to last commit
git revert commit_hash    # Undo commit safely
stash(save work temporarily):
git stash                 # Save work
git stash pop             # Restore saved work
PullRequests (Github):
-push your branch
git push origin branch_name
-Open a pull request from your branch into main
-commit often with clear messages
-keep feature work in branches, merge via Pull Requests
***** Use got status often-----Your Best friend*****8
